    <statement><div><p>A scientific calculator displays a number as <m>{1.4e+8}</m> Use logarithms to determine its standard form in the form: 
<m> A \times 10^B </m> </p>

<p><fillin characters="15" name="ans1"/>  </p></div></statement>
    <solution><div><h3>Worked Solution</h3>

<p>We use logarithms to find the exponent B.</p>

<p><me>
\log_{10}({1.4e+8}) 
= \log_{10}({1.4}) + {8}
</me></p>

<p>Thus:</p>

<p><me>
A = {1.4}, \quad B = {8}.
</me></p>

<p>Therefore the standard form is:</p>

<p><me>
{1.4} \times 10^{8}.
</me></p></div></solution>
    <answer><p><m>1.4e+8</m></p></answer>
</stack-static>